#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:2
msgid "Advanced Permissions (E10/E20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:4
msgid ""
"Advanced permissions offer Admins a way to restrict actions in Mattermost"
" to authorized users only. The Mattermost permission system is based on a"
" modified RBAC (role-based access control) architecture and will be "
"rolled out over a number of server releases, starting with Mattermost "
"server v5.0. The permissions interface can be accessed in **System "
"Console > User Management > Permissions** (or **System Console > Advanced"
" Permissions** in versions prior to 5.12)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:8
msgid ""
"This document applies to Mattermost Server version 5.0 and later. For "
"previous versions, see `permission settings available in the System "
"Console > Policy page <https://docs.mattermost.com/administration/config-"
"settings.html#policy>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:17
msgid "Permissions Structure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:19
msgid ""
"The Mattermost System Console provides a number of elements for Admins to"
" control the permissions in their system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:23
msgid "System Scheme (E10)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:25
msgid "*Available in Enterprise Edition E10 and higher*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:27
msgid ""
"You can set the default permissions granted to System Admins, Team "
"Admins, Channel Admins, Guests (if enabled), and All Members. The "
"permissions granted in the System Scheme apply system-wide, meaning:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:29
msgid ""
"**Guests:** If Guest Accounts are enabled, permissions apply to guest "
"users in all channels, in all teams."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:30
msgid ""
"**All Members:** Permissions apply to all members, including Admins, in "
"all channels, in all teams."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:31
msgid ""
"**Channel Administrators:** Permissions apply to all Channel Admins in "
"all channels, in all teams."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:32
msgid ""
"**Team Administrators:** Permissions apply to all Team Admins, in all "
"teams."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:34
msgid ""
"To override the System Scheme default permissions in a specific team, you"
" must set up a Team Override Scheme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:36
msgid "**System Scheme Interface**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:38
msgid ""
"The interface for editing permissions in the System Scheme, with panels "
"for Guests (if enabled), All Members, Channel Administrators, Team "
"Administrators, and System Administrators is available in **System "
"Console > User Management > Permissions > System Scheme** (or **System "
"Console > Advanced Permissions > System Scheme** in versions prior to "
"5.12)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:43
msgid "Team Override Schemes (E20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:45
msgid "*Available in Enterprise Edition E20*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:47
msgid ""
"Using these permissions overrides the default System Scheme permissions "
"in specific teams for All Members, Channel Adminstrators, and Team "
"Administrators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:49
msgid ""
"The permissions granted in a Team Override Scheme apply only in the teams"
" which are assigned to the scheme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:50
msgid ""
"The System Scheme does not apply to teams that are added to a Team "
"Override Scheme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:51
msgid "Teams can only belong to one Team Override Scheme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:53
msgid "**Team Override Schemes Interface**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/advanced-permissions.rst:55
msgid ""
"The interface for naming, assigning teams, and editing permissions in a "
"Team Override Scheme, with panels for All Members, Channel "
"Administrators, and Team Administrators is available in **System Console "
"> User Management > Permissions > Team Override Schemes** (or **System "
"Console > Advanced Permissions > Permissions Schemes > Team Override "
"Scheme** in versions prior to 5.12)."
